<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="832" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763 72112/1729</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Board Trade decides to make final settlements purchased American
                                cotton not covered by sale contracts, at market value at port of
                                shipment at date of shipment, plus all expenses, including freight,
                                insurance, war risk, and interest. In making settlements actual
                                contracts made about same date will be taken as further guide to
                                arrive at fair price to shippers.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>